The paper deals with proving the correctness of highly concurrent data structures, which suggests that it belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The specific focus on search data structures and traversal suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of sequential reasoning and local view arguments suggests that it may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The emphasis on acyclicity and preservation of search paths suggests that it may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Finally, the focus on establishing clear and comprehensible correctness proofs suggests that it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
